Talk to Sahaja Yogis from Africa, Swiss Hotel, Istanbul, 23.04.2001
Shri Mataji : You should not come to the poor people because to live with the nature
Yogi : Mais ça, ça ne doit pas arriver à vous parce que vous êtes au contact de la nature et les personnes naturelles ne sont jamais corrompues.
Shri Mataji : You know every leaf will be amazed which is a luxury, every leaf gets the sunshine.
Yogi :Chaque feuille reçoit la lumière du soleil.
Shri Mataji : Every leaf is different in the world, every leaf. And the way they organize is in such a manner, all of them get the sunlight.
Yogi :Et donc, tout est tellement bien organisé que chaque feuille reçoit la lumière.
Shri Mataji : But in corruption, one wants to have all in everything.
Yogi :Mais dans la corruption, il y a toujours un qui veut avoir tout.
Shri Mataji :  And then,
Yogi :Ramasser.
Shri Mataji : they don't know what is the joy in giving to others.
Yogi :Et alors ils ne peuvent pas comprendre la joie de donner aux autres.
Shri Mataji : See, that’s how it happens with Sahaja Yoga, to become extremely generous.
Yogi :Et ça, c’est ce qui nous arrive à Sahaja Yoga, on devient tres généreux.
Shri Mataji : I’ll give the example of my husband. Or I should say of my father.
Yogi :Je donne l'exemple de mon père.
Shri Mataji : He was a very very generous man, very.
Yogi :Il était un homme tres tres généreux.
Shri Mataji : And he told us not to lock the house. Keep it open, no thief will come.
Yogi :Et il a toujours dit de ne pas fermer la maison.
Shri Mataji : But one night a thief came and he took away this big gramophone which had this big horns, an old one  and he took off.
Yogi :Une nuit il y avait un voleur dans la maison et il a ramené, apporté un gramophone.
Shri Mataji :  And on the second day my father was upset. He was very upset.
Yogi :Et le jours apres mon père etait un peu... desolé.
Shri Mataji : So my mother said: “Is it because of the gramophone?”, “Is it because of the gramophone you are upset?”
Yogi :Alors sa mère lui demandé “Est-ce que c’est à cause de gramophone que t’es un peu dérangé?”
Shri Mataji : He said, “No, we can buy. But what about this man taking here no records, what would he use?”
Yogi : “C’est pas à cause de gramophone parce qu’on peut la remplacer. Mais le voleur, il n’a pas pris des disques.”
Shri Mataji : My mother said, “Alright.” And he said, “He should have brought somebody else to take the gramophone.”
Yogi : “Il [aurait dû] apporter quelqu’un d’autre pour ramasser disques.”
Shri Mataji :  So my mother said “Alright”, “What should we advertise in the newspaper? One who has stolen the gramophone can also take away the records.”
Yogi :Alors la mère de Shri Mataji dit, “Tu peut mettre l’avertissement sur le journal, en disant ceux qui ont apporté le gramophone peuvent venir chercher les disques.”
Shri Mataji : That kind of generosity it is, that kind. He said, we can afford to buy a booth, [...] of music, he should have records.
Yogi :Ca, c’est le [...] de générosité, parce que, eux, ils auraient pu remplacer le gramophone mai le voleur mais le voleur n’aurait pas.
Shri Mataji : Very generous, extremely generous.
Yogi :Il était un homme très généreux.
Shri Mataji : So, you see, the generosity is the only way we can correct [corruption]
Yogi :Et donc, à travers la générosite, nous pouvons effacer la corruption.
Shri Mataji :  When you start enjoying giving, you don't grab.
Yogi :Quand vous réjouissez donner les choses, vous ne cherchez pas de le ramasser.
Shri Mataji : And such a person has no reputation in the society, and that money that he grabs is of no use.
Yogi :Parce qu’un voleur, une personne corrompue, n’a jamais une réputation dans le pays pour le future.
Shri Mataji :  And all those people who have made money like that, have lost it when they put in this Swiss Bank.
Yogi :Et tous les gens qui ont fait ça, après on perdu le hasard, parce qu’ils ont mis à une banque suisse.
Shri Mataji : And the swiss bank also does not have [...] hit. They can give so much good but they don't, they are keeping all the money, they are sitting on top.
Yogi :Et les banques suisses, avec tous ces argents, ils peuvent faire quelque chose de bien, mais ils ne font pas, ils sont assis sur ça.
Shri Mataji : So one must, if say anything, talk about the swiss bank. Stop the swiss bank. It’s cheating, complete cheating.
Yogi :Si vous voulez dire quelque chose, si vous pouvez dire, arrêtez les banques suisses. Parce que c’est vraiment un moyen pour le... [tricherie].
Shri Mataji :  I don’t know how they are legalized, they take money from the thieves and keep it there. How can they do that?
Yogi :Et on comprend pas comment ca peut être légalisé. Parce que, bien sur, ils prennent tous ces argent de voleurs et... [le gardent].
Shri Mataji :  If you stop the working of the swiss bank, the corruption will go away.
Yogi :Et si on arrive à arrêter les banques suisses, les voleurs vont aussi disparaître.
Shri Mataji :  That’s the only way you can stop this high-class corruption.
Yogi :Ça, c’est le seul moyen pour arrêter la corruption a ce niveau.
Shri Mataji : You should write, you should write them all.
[...]
Shri Mataji : Americans are very careful. If you send any money from America to Switzerland, Switzerland informs the authorities.
Yogi :Les Américains sont intelligents parce que si quelqu’un cherche d’envoyer argent depuis Amerique en Suisse,  les Suisse informent les Américains, les autorités.
Shri Mataji : There in Brazil, I met with the minister of law and... justice, chief justice, both of them.
Yogi :Shri Mataji a rencontré le ministre de justice au Brésil.
Shri Mataji : They were very respectful but they said that in our country we had a prime minister who was a beast.
Yogi :Et, ils étaient très respectueux vers Shri Mataji, et ils on dit que a leur pays, ils on vu un ministre qui était, disons, un condamné [un monstre].
Shri Mataji : And that fellow has now a very great job in the University of... Harvard, Harvard University; teaching Economics.
Yogi :Et ce ministre voleur,  a reçu un job très important de l'Université de Harvard, pour enseigner Économiques.
Shri Mataji : He was impeached.
Yogi :Il etait, sous jugement, malgré ça.
Shri Mataji : All these thieves will be going to these kinds of universities, and they will teach our children how to cheat.
Yogi :Tous ces voleurs seront allés à ces grandes universités, pour apprendre nos enfants à voler.
Shri Mataji : That’s what is coming.
Yogi :C’est ce que ce passe.
Shri Mataji : I spoke about it in China, where they had this women conference.
Yogi :Shri Mataji a parlé de ça dans son discours en Chine.
Shri Mataji : But I don’t know, this is a big game going on.
Yogi :Et ça, c’est un grand jeu qui se joue.
Shri Mataji : And it’s a thing to be seen from Sahaja.
Yogi :Et il faut le voir avec un vue Sahaja. Dans un angle Sahaja.
Shri Mataji : And it will all work out alright, I am sure.
Yogi :Je suis sûre que tout va se régler, ameliorer.
Shri Mataji : Because it’s a global work.
Yogi :Parce que c’est un travail global.
Shri Mataji : So, it can not fail.
Yogi :Donc, elle ne peut pas faillir.
Shri Mataji : Because of the power of the collective.
Yogi :Parce que, est soutenue par le pouvoir de la collectivité.
Shri Mataji : I wish we could have a conference one day, with all of you in India or a new country.
Yogi : Yes, Shri Mataji, you should go there, you should go once in a big conference there.
